<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,528,1635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1393,1419]" pageId="2" pageNumber="566">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species is derived from Latin word “borealis” referring its northerly distribution in Asia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,528,1635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1465,1491]" pageId="2" pageNumber="566">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Duan, 2011" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Duan. A" authorityYear="2011" box="[589,959,1465,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangae">
<emphasis box="[589,709,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="566">M. yangae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Duan, Y. N." box="[716,959,1465,1491]" pageId="2" pageNumber="566" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref10189" refString="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Duan, Y. N. (2011) Review of the Deltocephalus group of leafhoppers (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae). Zootaxa, 2870 (1), 1 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2870.1.1" type="journal article" year="2011">Zhang &amp; Duan, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be readily differentiated from the latter by the style apophysis in having gently tapered apex and armed with a ventral tooth on subapex. Although it is abruptly tapered to apex from mid length, with a ventral tooth on next middle portion in the latter species. This species is also simlilar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Then, 1896)" authorityName="Then" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Then" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[396,681,1573,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis box="[396,528,1573,1599]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="566">M. horvathi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Then, F." box="[541,674,1573,1600]" pageId="2" pageNumber="566" pagination="165 - 179" refId="ref9996" refString="Then, F. (1896) Neue Arten der Cicadinen-Gattungen Deltocephalus and Thamnotettix. Mitteilungen Naturwissenschaftliche Vereines fur Steiermark, 32, 165 - 179, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1896">Then, 1896</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from the latter in having a somewhat broader aedeagal shaft, less acute aedeagal apex and shorter style apophysis.
</paragraph>
